******
[4] Media reports

Economic effects, regional
-----------------
29 Aug 2014: The African Development Bank (AfDB) has assessed that the worst ever EVD outbreak has been causing enormous damage to West African economies, as foreign businessmen quit the region. ...
http://allafrica.com/stories/201408290339.html

Sierra Leone: strike averted
----------------------
31 Aug 2014: (AP) In Sierra Leone on Sunday [31 Aug 2014], officials said they had avoided a strike threatened by workers at an EVD treatment center [Kenema] in the east of the country, the region hardest hit by the outbreak. Protective equipment is being sent to the health workers and a "monthly incentive allowance" will be paid on Mon [1 Sep 2014], health ministry spokesman Sidie Yahya Tunis told The Associated Press. On Fri [29 Aug 2014], Sierra Leone President Ernest Bai Koroma replaced Health Minister Miatta Kargbo with Abu Bakarr Fofanah, a move his office described as necessary to more efficiently combat the outbreak. Kargbo was recalled to work in the president's office. http://bigstory.ap.org/article/who-senegal-ebola-case-top-priority-emergency

[In Kenema, 26 staff members have already died from EVD, following the death of physician Sahr Rogers. The diagnostic lab has been closed down, and some international staff have been withdrawn after safety concerns. - Mod.JW]

